# Apply chosen fixes

The skill under review is at `{{ vars.skill_dir }}`. The audit
report is at `{{ vars.report_path }}`. The user's choices for
this pass are in the `skill-fix-review` output at:

`{{ upstream['skill-fix-review'].task_path }}`

It has two lists: `items` (findings to fix, each with an
`instruction`) and `dismissed` (findings to close without a
change).

## Steps

1. For each entry in `items`:
   - Apply the fix to the skill at `{{ vars.skill_dir }}` following
     the user's `instruction`. Edit the real skill files.
   - Mark the finding fixed in the report:
     `{{ vars.dojo_sh }} report accept {{ run.workdir }} <finding_id>`
2. For each `finding_id` in `dismissed`:
   - Close it without a code change:
     `{{ vars.dojo_sh }} report decline {{ run.workdir }} <finding_id> --reason "<short reason>"`
3. Recompute the open count:
   `{{ vars.dojo_sh }} report open-count {{ run.workdir }}`
   This returns `{open_items: N}` — findings still lacking a ✅/⏩
   marker.

## Output

Write `{{ task.output_path }}` matching
`schemas/skill_fix_apply.yaml`:

```bash
{{ vars.loom_sh }} output init {{ run.workdir }} --task skill-fix-apply
{{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} --task skill-fix-apply \
    --set open_items=<N from report open-count> \
    --set files='["<changed file>", ...]'
```

If `open_items > 0`, the loop returns to `show-report` for another
pass; when it reaches 0 the loop exits to `finalize`. Only apply
what the user asked for this pass — do not fix or dismiss findings
they did not choose.
